frameDefinitions: There exist a number of different possible Situations that may happen in the future.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.

An Agent has attempted to achieve a Goal, and the actual outcome of the Agent's action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Agent's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
An Event takes place at a Place and Time.
This frame describes a complex event which lasts some amount of time, consisting of a beginning stage, a stage where the process is ongoing, and a finish or end.

The Means action by which a deprofiled agent (the Protagonist) has attempted to achieve a Goal, is finished and the actual outcome of the Means action has been resolved, so that it either specifically matches the Protagonist's intent (e.g. success) or does not match it (e.g. failure).
frameExamples: You have but two <t><fex name='Situation'>choices</fex></t> for your daughter .
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
He <t>pulled</t> <t>off</t> his April Fool's Day prank by the barest of margins .
Big earthquakes only <t>happen</t> along plate boundaries. INI
I'm in the <t>process</t> of writing it down.
listRoleDefinitions: Something that may happen in the future, or at least whose factual status is unresolved. This is often tagged in a second role layer and generally contains the target.

An individual involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.

'<fex name='Agent'>You</fex> have a <t>choice</t>.'
An entity intimately involved in the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
A participant function in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails.
The place where an attempt succeeds or fails.
Name of the event which occurs.
Where the event takes place.
When the event occurs.
Name of the Process which occurs.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The action that the agent undertakes to achieve the <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the agent attempts to achieve by performing the <fen>Means</fen> action.
An entity directed by the agent as part of the <fen>Means</fen> action in order to accomplish the <fen>Goal</fen>.
A participant function of an <fen>Instrument</fen> or <fen>Means</fen> in a particular event or in events of a particular kind.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt succeeds or fails
The place where <fen>Means</fen> action succeeds or fails.
